#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Pepco Holdings Inc.

is set to get a $30 million tax refund from Maryland as a result of a settlement with the state, the Washington utility company said Monday. The refund stems from a correction of the tax basis for generation assets Pepco sold in 2000, the company said in its second-quarter report filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission. Pepco said it will record the refund in the third quarter.
